    <!-- Background grid pattern -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-[0.03] pointer-events-none">
      <svg width="100%" height="100%" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
        <defs>
          <pattern
            id="features-grid"
            width="32"
            height="32"
            patternUnits="userSpaceOnUse"
          >
            <path
              d="M 32 0 L 0 0 0 32"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="1"></path>
          </pattern>
        </defs>
        <rect width="100%" height="100%" fill="url(#features-grid)"></rect>
      </svg>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Introduction Section -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-background">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-display font-bold text-text mb-6">
          Data-Driven Scheduling Decisions
        </h2>
        <div
          class="prose prose-lg max-w-none space-y-6 text-text-muted leading-relaxed"
        >
          <p>
            Real-time dashboard transforms scheduling data into actionable
            insights that drive business decisions. Every booking, cancellation,
            and rescheduling updates KPIs instantly, giving you current
            performance visibility rather than outdated reports from last week
            or last month. See exactly how many appointments were booked today,
            which team members have highest utilization rates, and what revenue
            you've generated this quarter without waiting for manual report
            compilation. Dashboard metrics refresh automatically as calendar
            activity happens, eliminating lag between business events and
            performance awareness.
          </p>

          <p>
            Appointment analytics reveal booking patterns that manual schedule
            review would never surface. Visualizations show which days have
            highest booking volume, what times prospects prefer for meetings,
            and how far in advance clients typically schedule. These patterns
            inform strategic decisions about availability optimization, staffing
            allocation, and marketing campaign timing. When you notice Thursday
            afternoons consistently book heavy while Monday mornings stay empty,
            you can adjust available slots to match demand patterns. Analytics
            turn calendar data from passive record-keeping into active business
            intelligence.
          </p>

          <p>
            Revenue tracking connects scheduling directly to financial outcomes
            by monitoring income from paid appointments. Dashboard calculates
            total revenue from completed bookings, forecasts future income based
            on scheduled appointments, and tracks conversion rates from free
            consultations to paid engagements. This financial visibility helps
            service businesses understand booking quality beyond quantity
            metrics. A hundred free discovery calls mean less than twenty
            high-value consulting engagements. Revenue analytics ensure you
            optimize for profitable bookings rather than just appointment
            volume.
          </p>

          <p>
            Team performance metrics provide coaching insights by comparing
            individual booking rates and utilization across team members. See
            which salespeople convert highest percentage of prospects, which
            consultants maintain fullest schedules, and which support reps
            handle most client appointments. Performance data identifies both
            excellence to replicate and struggles requiring coaching
            intervention. When one team member books twice as many meetings as
            colleagues, you can analyze their availability patterns and booking
            link usage to share best practices across the organization.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How It Works Section -->
  <section class="py-32 relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="container relative z-10">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
        <!-- Badge -->
        <div
